<TEXT>
<P>
Canada tied Finland, 3-3, in the World Junior hockey championship at Helsinki 
and must win its three remaining games to win the gold medal for the fourth 
time. 
</P>
<P>
Canada plays the Soviet Union today, Sweden on Wednesday and ends the 
eight-nation, round-robin tournament against Czechoslovakia on Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
In the other game Sunday, Sweden routed Poland, 14-0. 
</P>
<P>
The Soviets and Czechoslovaks are tied for first with four victories apiece. 
They meet on Tuesday in what most observers feel will be the match for the gold 
medal. 
</P>
<P>
Canada is in third place, Sweden in fourth. 
</P>
